column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
clear sky no clouds- .10 " of rain last night 85 degrees and muggy
.25 " of rain yesterday- no rain since last reading.82 degrees and muggy. some light algea beads on surface. I believe this is because of lack of rain.
clear sky- 2.00 inches of rain since last reading 72 degrees. Secchi dish did not hit bottom before sight gone for first time. It was half of a foot off of the bottom.
68 degrees no clouds- bright sun. very little rain since last reading. 9.0 feet of water at site.
Mostly sunny 70 degrees. 1/2" of rain yesterday. 10' of water at test site. One dead bullhead floating on the surface.
bright sun- no clouds. calm- no wind. 1/4" of rain since last reading clear skies- no clouds. calm- no wind. 1/4" of rain since last reading. 10.25' of water.
62 degrees- little wind- 1/2" of rain since last reading. 10.25 feet of water at site. water color is getting closer to blue with little rain.
cool- 50 degrees. few clouds. no rain since last reading. borrowed DO and temp meter for additional data.
cloudy no sun. 1/2" of rain yesterday 10' of water at test site

50 degrees. intermitent rain. 1 " of rain since last reading. Cloud and sun. Had Sandra Wickman from the DNR here to do DO and PH readings as well as conductivity. Thanks. It appears that the abuntant plant life is starting to decompose as Do has gone down from 2 weeks ago.
I tried to to do secchi reading on 10/07/2011- but with 35 MPH winds- I could not hold the boat. Today is mostly cloudy- temp 48 degrees and NW winds. 2" of rain yesterday.
First reading of year. Ice off on March 20- 2012. Earliest ever in 60 years.
1/2" of rain on the 2nd. Sunny out . 55 degrees
Hazy sun- 68 degrees 1" of rain on the 3rd. water level a little above normal. hazy sun- 68 degrees 1 inch of rain on 3rd lake level up a little above normal.10.25'  of water at test sight
sunny- 80 degrees- and very windy 10' of water at test site
cloudy with hazy sun- 66 degrees. light wind. Since last reading we have had 1" of rain and 2 days of extremely high winds up to 50mph. 10' of water at test site.
3 1/2 inches of rain at one time since last reading. 68 degrees- sunny- light wind. Some pine pollen on surface of water. 10.75 feet of water at test sight.
72 degrees- sunny with wind. Have had strong winds for three days. 10.5 feet of water at site.

78 degrees- humid- hazy sun. Had 0.3 inch of rain early this morning with 1.25" yesterday. Strong thunderstorms the last 2 days. We have seen 2 loon chicks so far this year. If the eagles leave them alone- maybe we can fledge both of them this year.

hazy sunshine 72 degrees. we have had 3" of rain since last reading. water level just slightly up from normal. still have 2 loon chicks and others have told me that we have 32 pair of loons and the other pair has one chick. I haven't seen this yet. it seems odd that we would have 2 nesting pairs on a 300 acre lake. we never ahve before.

sunny-85 degrees. 11 feet of water at lest site. Has been extremely hot this week with highs in the 90's and high humidity. Some weeds blown into shore line areas from heavier boat traffic cuttting them off. No invasives- but weeds all the same.
82 degrees- sunny and humid. Some algea is appearing near shore with this hot weather and little breeze or rain.Loon chicks are getting bigger and should survive the eagle attacks.
85 degrees.sunny. Weeds floating in lake. Lake appears to be down about 4-6".
sunny 83 degrees. we had 4.5" of rain in one day since last reading. Still some weeds blowing in from boat traffic.
I missed last week and found quite a change.
82 degrees- sunny with light wind from the sounthwest. Very little rain as of late.
92 degrees- windy. Haven't had much rain in the last 3 weeks. Lake is down about 6-8".
64 degrees and coudy. we got 1/4" of rain last night- the first rain in nearly 4 weeks. Lake still down about 8-10"
54 degrees- mostly cloudy. lake down about 10-12". need rain 54 degrees- mostly cloudy. Lake down nearly 12" need rain. water is very clear- secchi is still white at one foot mark.
sunny- 65 degrees- no wind. In 23 summers living on the lake i have never seen the water this low or this clear.we need a good rain
3 loon seen on the lake. nice to finally get out and check things out again.
Has been raining for what seems like forever. temps are still cool for this time of year. today is cloudy with breaks of sun and about 58 degrees.
hazy sunshine- 68 degrees. We have not had rain for nearly a week. I believe that is the longest stretch of dry weather we have had since January. At least it seems that way.
sunny- 68 degrees. it looks like we might get a 3-4 day stretch of no rain. badly needed.
Mostly sunny- 82 degrees. Had 1/2 inch of rain last night. First rain in nearly a week. weeds are coming up near surface now.

70 degrees- partly cloudy. Nice to have decent temps after last weeks heat wave. Haven't had rain in almost 2 weeks. I saw two herons while out and decided to take a fishing rod along. Caught a 25" Northern pike on the first cast. Several hits- but no more fish. Fresh fish for supper tonight.
78 degrees- sunny and quite windy. lake is down around 7 inches and we haven't had rain in quite some time.
sunny- 68 degrees. we have had 4 inches of rain in the last week.
partly cloudy- 80 degrees. We've had just a slight shower since last reading.
Frost has put and end to the garden. Leaves are changing and falling. Fall is in the  air-- but some really nice weather now. 70 degrees and sunny. Light wind.

Lake is very high- 8-10" above normal. Ice went out on April 29- 2014. Lots of ducks and the loons are back. It appears that we had a little bit of winter kill. I have seen one bass- a couple of bullheads and a few gills.

windy- 80 degrees. some pine pollen on the lake surface. hasn't rained for some time. lake level is back to normal finally. Pair of geese with 4 little ones hanging around with the mess that comes with them.
hazy sunshine- 74 degrees. very little rain in last week. geese still hanging around shoreline with 4 little ones. They need to go.
partly cloudy- 68 degrees. no rain today- .20" of rain yesterday. Nearly 2" since last reading.
no wind- 69 degrees. Had a 2" downpour on the 4th that brought water levels up
On Thursday we had over 4" of rain. Lake is as high or higher than the spring melt.
partly cloudy- 68 degrees. Had 0.4" of rain last night
Had 1.75 " of rain again this past week and 1.5" of snow on the 4th of October. Today is 55 degrees and mostly cloudy.
55 degrees and sunny. Beautiful fall day. Will be last reading for this year- as I finally took the last boat out.
We had 2 inches of rain yesterday. mostly sunny and 75 degrees
partly cloudy- 74 degrees. had .36"  of rain yesterday
Happy summer- also fathers day. 68 degrees partly sunny. had 0.3" of rain yesterday. It seems to rain every other day around here.
mostly sunny. 78 degrees. 7 days now and only 0.11" of rain. the driest stretch all year.
0.5" of rain yesterday. Sunny and 85 degrees. Has been very hot and humid. A little bit of algae on the surface.
Some sun and clouds. 72 degrees and 10-15mph winds. We have had 2.25" of rain this week and the water has darken greatly.
cloudy and 67 degrees. beautiful weather for this time  of year. Lots of ducks showing up. Might make the duck hunters happy this weekend.
1.15 inches of rain yesterday. First real rain in quite a while. Filtered sun- 65 degrees
sunny 78 degrees- light wind. We have had a lot of rain this spring- nearly 5" in the last week and half.
76 degrees- partly sunny with light SE wind.
mostly sunny- 84 degrees with light wind. I had my hip replaced 4 weeks ago- so haven't been able to do readings as I would like.
calm- 78 degrees humid and partly cloudy. went fishing with wife and caught a meal of bluegills.
calm winds- mostly cloudy- 71 degrees. got to go fishing for a short while- fish didn't cooperate very well- though
Nice day for October- temp 68 degree- with light southeast wind. Still saw our young of the year loon.

56 degrees and mostly sunny. last reading of the year. took a short ride on the lake and pulling the pontoon out today. seems like I just put it in. Sad- but summer Is over. Looking forward to some great snowmobiling this winter. 56 degrees and mostly sunny. had 5' of rain last week on Monday. went for a short pontoon ride and then pulled it out for the winter. seems like I just put it in. Looking forwards to some great snowmobiling this winter.
sunny 51 degrees- We have had so much rain that everything is high and swamps are overfull.
74 degrees and rare sunshine. It rains most every day. 12+" ahead of normal rainfall this year. Rivers and lakes are very high.
mostly sunny- 75 degrees and the fish are biting
sunny- 60 degrees. had 2.75" of rain on 10/7/17. Took our last pontoon ride for the season and saw 2 swans on the lake.
ice finished coming off today about 11 AM. Sunny light breeze 66 degrees
With less than half inch of rain since ice off- the water is getting clearer. Temps today at 87 with sun and light breeze.

We had a large amount of rain last weekend and the lake has come up considerably. 80 degrees and mostly sunny. I have put swan decoys in our bay to try to keep the geese away. They work very well. Last week a lone swan came into the decoys and has been hanging around for almost 2 weeks. I assume that it is looking for a mate- but good luck with the plastic ones in the bay. At least they must look real.

partly cloudy 74 degrees. has been very hot with little rain. lake is down about 5". DO reading were taken at deep hole. water was calm and we have not had any wind the last several days. I took reading out in the windy part of the lake and the levels were slightly higher in the top two feet.ds
cloudy- 50 degrees no wind. have had 3 inches of rain last 3 days.
mostly sunny- 77 degrees. We had 2 inches rain over the weekend and darkened the water some. Needed rain- we dodged the bad winds and hail thank god
Just put pontoon in the water and did first reading of the year.
77 degrees mostly sunny with light winds.
Last reading of the year. Putting pontoon away for the winter. Sad day.
